Research is somewhat helpful.  I tried to keep mine up for a awhile through regular runes and practice runes, but after you get past the level 49 spells the trivials are pretty high.  You will have to invest quite a bit of time, money, or skill points to get up to 200. (Which I did)
It was nice to be able to research my level 60 spells for less investment than they were selling for in the bazaar. I have even been able to sell a few spells I researched myself for wizzies and priest classes.

However, bear in mind, once you get past level 60, your spells are no longer researchable.  Research becomes a bit less valuable at that point, except to make a little money on the side if you pay attention.

